The paper deals with the optimization of autonomous vehicle driving through the joint adaptation of communications and motion planning. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves the use of autonomous vehicles. The paper also deals with networking and communication (cs.NI) as it focuses on the use of infrastructure to query sensed information. The use of reinforcement learning (RL) to optimize the driving utility of the vehicle places the paper under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with systems and control (cs.SY) as it involves the control of the vehicle's motion planning. Finally, the use of RL algorithms to learn the optimal policy places the paper under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
